import React from "react";
import { useParams } from "react-router-dom";

function ProjectDetails() {
  const { id } = useParams();

  return (
    <div style={{ padding: "50px", textAlign: "center" }}>
      {id === "resume" && (
        <>
          <h1>AI Based Resume Builder</h1>
          <p>
            Here is the **detailed explanation** of your **AI-Based Resume Builder Project**:

The AI-Based Resume Builder is an intelligent web application designed to help job seekers create professional, well-structured, and ATS-friendly resumes efficiently. In today’s competitive job market, many candidates struggle to prepare resumes that properly highlight their skills and match job requirements. This project solves that problem by integrating Artificial Intelligence (AI), Machine Learning (ML), and Natural Language Processing (NLP) to automate and optimize resume creation.

The system allows users to enter their personal information, education details, work experience, skills, projects, certifications, and additional links through a user-friendly interface built using Streamlit. Once the user provides the required data and selects the job role they are applying for, the AI engine analyzes the input and generates professional content such as a summary, job descriptions, and skill explanations.

The application uses NLP techniques to analyze job descriptions and extract important keywords. These keywords are then matched with the user’s profile to ensure the resume is optimized for Applicant Tracking Systems (ATS). This increases the chances of the resume being shortlisted by recruiters.

The system also provides a resume feedback and scoring feature. It evaluates the resume based on relevance, clarity, technical skills, formatting, and completeness. It identifies missing components such as key technical skills (e.g., SQL, Python, ETL, Data Modeling) and suggests improvements. Real-time grammar checking and content refinement are also included.

Technically, the project consists of:

* Frontend: Streamlit-based user interface
* Backend: Python-based processing logic
* AI Engine: OpenAI API for content generation and feedback
* Document Processing: Markdown to HTML conversion and PDF generation using tools like PDFKit and wkhtmltopdf
* Database/Storage: For storing user inputs and generated resumes

The system architecture includes presentation, application, AI processing, and data layers to ensure scalability and performance. Security measures are implemented to protect user data.

The final output is a clean, professional resume that can be downloaded as a PDF. Overall, this project automates resume writing, improves quality, saves time, and significantly enhances a candidate’s chances of securing interviews.

          </p>
        </>
      )}

      {id === "retinopathy" && (
        <>
          <h1>Diabetic Retinopathy Detection System</h1>
          <p>
           This interface represents a **Diabetic Retinopathy Detection System** designed to analyze retinal fundus images using a hybrid deep-learning architecture that combines **DenseNet201 and ResNet50**. The system allows users to upload a retinal image (JPG, JPEG, or PNG format) through a drag-and-drop or browse option. Once the image is uploaded, the model processes it and extracts important retinal features such as blood vessel patterns, microaneurysms, hemorrhages, and exudates.

After analysis, the system predicts the stage of diabetic retinopathy and provides a confidence score. In the displayed example, the uploaded retinal image is classified as **Severe Diabetic Retinopathy** with a confidence of **57.05%**. This indicates that the model found significant retinal abnormalities associated with advanced disease progression.

The interface also presents detailed **class probabilities** for all five categories: No DR, Mild, Moderate, Severe, and Proliferative DR. These probabilities are visually represented using progress bars, making it easier to understand how strongly the model leans toward each class. Such transparency helps in interpreting the model’s decision rather than just showing a single label.

Overall, the system serves as an AI-powered screening and decision-support tool that can assist healthcare professionals in early detection and severity grading of diabetic retinopathy, potentially reducing the risk of vision loss through timely intervention.

          </p>
        </>
      )}
    </div>
  );
}

export default ProjectDetails;
